reviewText: Most boring  course I have ever done in my life one star is also over rated.
I have completed every portion of this course but it will not state that I finished it.

Somewhat helpful in terms of resume writing. I audited the course and therefore would have to upgrade to take quizzes, and get graded. I have no desire to do this so the class constantly is telling my I am missing deadlines, falling behind etc. I wish this would stop for those auditing the class, super frustrating!!!

This was an an excellent course as far as information shared in the videos and reading. I thought the idea of the exercises was good, however the Peer Reviews were not that helpful. Most of the participants were very young Newbies in search of their first job or first career post college. I am a 69 year-old laid off teacher (COVID19 and budget cuts), trying to get a job in another profession, for the last year of my working life. The peer critiques were lacking the fine tuning that I needed. I think it would be helpful  to get some actual professor grading in there. If that isn't possible, maybe a teaching assistant?That being said, I have a job interview this Thursday. Let's hope some of the pre-interview and interview tips help me land that job!Thank you for having these classes available!
v.good

It was a great push to start my career and to understand what I am going to face ahead in the future. Due to coursera it has made me realise that getting a job would sound easy but needs hard work and very good knowledge of what you are aiming for. I have also recommended this to my family & friends, very happy with the results.
